1 olive oil
1 bag mint
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet salmon
1 portion cauliflower
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 white turnip
1 Brown Onion
1 leek
1 packet freekeh
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Toast freekeh, stirring
occasionally, until golden, 1-2 minutes.
• Half-fill saucepan with water, then add a good
pinch of salt. Bring to the boil, then simmer,
uncovered, until tender, 30-35 minutes.
• Drain and rinse.

TIP: The freekeh is cooked when it has softened but
still retains some bite.

• Meanwhile, cut cauliflower into small florets.
Thickly slice leek. Cut white turnip into
bite-sized chunks. Cut onion into wedges.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic & herb
seasoning. Season with a pinch of salt and
pepper. Toss to coat, then roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, pick and roughly chop mint leaves.
• In a small bowl, combine Greek-style yoghurt
with a pinch of salt and pepper.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Pat salmon dry with
paper towel and season both sides.
• When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down
first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each
side.

TIP: Patting the skin dry helps it crisp up in the pan!

• To the freekeh, add the roasted veggies, mint,
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive
oil. Season to taste.

• Divide cauliflower freekeh cauliflower salad and
seared salmon between plates.
• Top with yoghurt to serve. Enjoy!